'''威尼斯鉛粉'''作為一種[[化妝品|化妝品]]被應用在不同的古代社會中，因為[[鉛白|鉛白]]的色澤是古代中其他白色顏料無可匹敵的。就算是人類開始認識到[[鉛|鉛]]對人體的[[鉛中毒|害處]]以來，還是有活躍於交際圈的人士出於當時社會追求雪白肌膚的[[審美|審美]]標準而繼續使用鉛粉[[化妝|化妝]]。

==古代中國==
古代中國應用鉛粉化妝參考宋代的《[[事物紀原|事物紀原]]》可以追溯至[[周朝|周朝]]，《[[琅嬛記|琅嬛記]]》亦提及了古人以鉛粉化妝及另一有毒物質—[[汞|汞]]用作為[[唇膏|唇膏]]，中文亦存在一些將鉛聯繫到化妝的成語例如「洗盡鉛華」。

==近世歐洲==
[[File:Maria_Coventry,_Countess_of_Coventry_(after_Francis_Cotes).jpg|thumb]]
16世紀[[近世|近世]]歐洲就有記載一款名為「'''威尼斯鉛粉'''」（{{lang-en|Venetian ceruse}}）的鉛白化妝品流行於歐洲各國的上流社會，威尼斯錫茹斯將[[碳酸鉛|碳酸鉛]]混合[[白醋|白醋]]、[[硼砂|硼砂]]、[[蜂蠟|蜂蠟]]或[[杏仁|杏仁]]油等材料使其容易塗抹和依附在肌膚上<ref name="Eldridge2015">{{Cite book |title=Face Paint: The Story of Makeup |author=Lisa Eldridge |publisher=Abrams |year=2015 |isbn=9781613128183 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=LpplCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT67}}</ref>。

認為雪白肌膚象徵處女的純潔的英女皇[[伊莉莎白一世|伊莉莎白一世]]就被謠傳長期使用威尼斯錫茹斯化妝<ref name="Thomas 2020 p. 26">{{cite book | last=Thomas | first=L.M. | title=Beneath the Surface: A Transnational History of Skin Lighteners | publisher=Duke University Press | series=Theory in Forms | year=2020 | isbn=978-1-4780-0705-0 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=A3C_DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT26 | access-date=2020-07-17 | page=pt26 | archive-date=2021-08-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210801234456/https://books.google.com/books?id=A3C_DwAAQBAJ&pg=PT26 | dead-url=no }}</ref>，但也有歷史學家反駁指證據不充分<ref name="Riehl2010">{{Cite book |author=Anna Riehl |title=The Face of Queenship: Early Modern Representations of Elizabeth I |year=2010 |isbn=9780230106741 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=CrzHAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA13}}</ref><ref name="Maltby2015">{{Cite web |url=http://www.katemaltby.com/why-is-elizabeth-i-the-most-powerful-woman-in-our-history-always-depicted-as-a-grotesque/ |title=Why is Elizabeth I always depicted as a grotesque? |date=2015-05-25 |website=Kate Maltby |access-date=2019-10-05 |quote=Even Venetian Ceruse, the notorious pale make-up used by Elizabethan actors and never found in the inventories of the queen herself, has been shown in reconstructions to blend lightly into the skin like a modern concealer... |archive-date=2018-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180303173702/http://www.katemaltby.com/why-is-elizabeth-i-the-most-powerful-woman-in-our-history-always-depicted-as-a-grotesque/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。肌膚不用因為出外進行長期勞動而被太陽曬黑，因此雪白膚色成為貴族的一種身分象徵，英國[[喬治時代|喬治時代]]家道中落的貴族後代{{le|瑪麗亞·考文垂|Maria Coventry, Countess of Coventry|瑪麗亞·根寧}}為了進駐倫敦的上流交際圈並嫁入貴族豪門，堅持使用鉛粉化妝，儘管於喬治時代歐洲人已經對[[鉛中毒|鉛中毒]]有了一定認知。瑪麗亞·根寧嫁給{{le|喬治·考文垂 (第六代考文垂伯爵)|George Coventry, 6th Earl of Coventry|考文垂伯爵}}後卒於27歲，死因被認為是鉛中毒<ref name="StClair">{{Cite book |author=Kassia St. Clair |title=The Secret Lives of Colour |publisher=John Murray |location=London |year=2016 |isbn=9781473630819 |page=45–46 |oclc=936144129}}</ref><ref name="Stewart2017">{{Cite book |author=Susan Stewart |title=Painted Faces: A Colourful History of Cosmetics |publisher=Amberley Publishing |date=2017 |isbn=9781445654003 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=PTBDDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT138}}</ref>。

